{
  "article_id": "Geiger1970",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Few events in the history of early ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " caused a greater stir and sensation than the discovery in 1853 of ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " on ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " who had lived there alone for eighteen years. And few events in Santa Barbara's long colorful history have engaged people's imagination and interest as much as the almost incredible story of ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Had this story been written as fiction it would have been rejected. But the story is true. ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The Franciscan padres of Mission Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " were involved in her discovery.",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Today they are involved in telling her story."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " lies out in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Pacific",
        "entity_key": "re_pacific",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " about seventy miles from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It is nine miles long and three and a half miles wide. It had been inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "from the earliest times. In 1811 "
      },
      {
        "text": "a ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_charon",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " belonging to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Pope and Boardman",
        "entity_key": "bp",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Boston",
        "entity_key": "ci_bo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", brought about thirty "
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiaks",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Russian Alaska",
        "entity_key": "re_russam",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to hunt otter and seal."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "They were left there with provisions to be picked up again in a year and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_charon",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " sailed further south. Meanwhile[,] a feud broke out between "
      },
      {
        "text": "the native Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " and the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiaks",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The majority of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the native men",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were killed by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the newcomers",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " [...]"
      }
    ]
  ]
}